Q3. What is COMBINE framework and how have you used it?
    WHY ASKED: Highly demanded since iOS 13 — every interviewer asks.

A:  "Combine is Apple's reactive programming framework.
    It lets you handle asynchronous events using Publishers
    and Subscribers.

    Key concepts:
    - Publisher  : Emits values over time
    - Subscriber : Receives and reacts to values
    - Operator   : Transforms values (map, filter, debounce)

    Example I used in Count My Calories:
    @Published var calorieInput: String = ''
    calorieInput publisher
        .debounce(for: 0.5, scheduler: RunLoop.main)
        .sink { value in self.calculateCalories(value) }

    This prevented recalculation on every keystroke —
    only triggered 0.5s after user stopped typing.
    Result: smoother UI and better performance."

