Q4. What is ASYNC/AWAIT in Swift and why is it better than closures?
    WHY ASKED: Most trending question in 2024-2025 market.

A:  "Async/Await (Swift 5.5+) makes asynchronous code
    look and behave like synchronous code — much cleaner
    than nested closures (callback hell).

    OLD WAY (closure):
    fetchPrayerTimes { times in
        fetchLocation { location in
            fetchQibla(location) { angle in
                // deeply nested — hard to read
            }
        }
    }

    NEW WAY (async/await):
    let times    = await fetchPrayerTimes()
    let location = await fetchLocation()
    let angle    = await fetchQibla(location)

    Benefits:
    - Linear, readable code
    - Built-in error handling with try/catch
    - No retain cycle issues with [weak self]

    I have refactored my Azaan Pro network calls to use
    async/await which reduced code by 40% and made
    debugging much easier."

