Q5. What are ACTORS in Swift Concurrency?
    WHY ASKED: New topic — senior developers are expected to know.

A:  "Actors are reference types that protect their state
    from data races in concurrent environments.

    Without actor — race condition possible:
    class Counter {
        var count = 0
        func increment() { count += 1 } // UNSAFE on multiple threads
    }

    With actor — thread safe:
    actor Counter {
        var count = 0
        func increment() { count += 1 } // SAFE — serialized access
    }

    MainActor is a special actor that ensures code runs
    on the main thread — perfect for UI updates.

    @MainActor func updateUI() {
        self.label.text = 'Updated'
    }

    I use @MainActor in my apps to guarantee all UI updates
    happen on the main thread without manual DispatchQueue calls."

