Q6. What is MEMORY MANAGEMENT and how do you prevent RETAIN CYCLES?
    WHY ASKED: Critical for senior roles — always asked.

A:  "iOS uses ARC (Automatic Reference Counting) to manage memory.
    A retain cycle happens when two objects hold strong references
    to each other — neither gets deallocated — causing memory leak.

    Common scenario — closure capturing self:
    class ViewModel {
        var completion: (() -> Void)?
        func load() {
            completion = {
                self.process() // RETAIN CYCLE — self holds completion
            }
        }
    }

    FIX — use [weak self]:
    completion = { [weak self] in
        self?.process() // safe — self can become nil
    }

    I always use [weak self] inside Firebase callbacks and
    URLSession completions in my apps. I also use Instruments
    — Memory Leak tool in Xcode — to verify zero leaks
    before App Store submission."

