Q7. What is GENERICS in Swift and where have you used it?
    WHY ASKED: Shows depth of Swift knowledge — asked in mid/senior roles.

A:  "Generics allow writing flexible, reusable functions
    that work with any type.

    Without generics — repeated code:
    func printInt(_ value: Int) { print(value) }
    func printString(_ value: String) { print(value) }

    With generics — one function for all types:
    func printValue<T>(_ value: T) { print(value) }

    Real use in my app:
    func saveToDefaults<T: Codable>(key: String, value: T) {
        let data = try? JSONEncoder().encode(value)
        UserDefaults.standard.set(data, forKey: key)
    }
    // Works for saving ANY Codable model

    This reusable function saved me from writing separate
    save functions for prayer times, calorie data, and
    user preferences in my apps."

