Q8. What is PROPERTY WRAPPERS in Swift?
    WHY ASKED: SwiftUI heavily uses them — very common question.

A:  "@State, @Binding, @ObservedObject, @Published are
    all property wrappers.

    Property wrappers add behavior to a property automatically.

    @Published — notifies observers when value changes:
    class UserSettings: ObservableObject {
        @Published var dailyCalorieGoal: Int = 2000
    }

    @State — local state in SwiftUI view:
    @State private var isLoading = false

    @AppStorage — auto syncs with UserDefaults:
    @AppStorage('username') var username = ''

    In my Count My Calories app, I used @Published on
    calorie goal and @AppStorage for user preferences —
    eliminating manual UserDefaults save/load code."

