Q9. What is the difference between SwiftUI and UIKit?
    WHY ASKED: Every company is moving to SwiftUI — must know.

A:  "UIKit: Imperative — you describe HOW to change UI
    SwiftUI: Declarative — you describe WHAT the UI should look like

    UIKit (imperative):
    label.text = 'Hello'
    label.textColor = .red

    SwiftUI (declarative):
    Text('Hello').foregroundColor(.red)

    SwiftUI advantages:
    - Less code (up to 70% less boilerplate)
    - Live Preview in Xcode
    - Automatic dark mode, dynamic type support
    - Works across iOS, macOS, watchOS

    I have experience in UIKit and am actively building
    new features using SwiftUI. Both my personal projects
    started with UIKit and I have migrated components to
    SwiftUI progressively."

