Q10. What is @State, @Binding, @ObservableObject in SwiftUI?
     WHY ASKED: Core SwiftUI — asked in every iOS interview now.

A:  "@State — private local state, owned by one view:
    @State private var count = 0

    @Binding — two-way connection to parent's state:
    @Binding var isPresented: Bool
    (child view reads and writes parent's value)

    @ObservableObject + @Published — shared state across
    multiple views:
    class CalorieViewModel: ObservableObject {
        @Published var totalCalories: Int = 0
    }

    @EnvironmentObject — inject shared model deep in
    view hierarchy without passing it manually.

    Think of it like:
    @State        = your own notebook
    @Binding      = borrowed notebook from parent
    @ObservableObject = shared notebook everyone reads/writes"

