Q11. What is the difference between @ObservableObject and @Observable?
     WHY ASKED: New in iOS 17 — very trending in 2025 interviews.

A:  "@ObservableObject (iOS 13+):
    - Class must conform to ObservableObject protocol
    - Must manually mark properties with @Published
    - Used with @StateObject, @ObservedObject

    @Observable (iOS 17+, Swift 5.9):
    - Just add @Observable macro to class
    - ALL stored properties auto-tracked — no @Published needed
    - Simpler, better performance

    OLD (ObservableObject):
    class ViewModel: ObservableObject {
        @Published var name = ''
        @Published var calories = 0
    }

    NEW (Observable macro):
    @Observable class ViewModel {
        var name = ''
        var calories = 0  // auto-tracked
    }

    I am familiar with both approaches and have adopted
    @Observable in my latest project updates targeting iOS 17+."

