Q12. What is LazyVStack vs VStack in SwiftUI?
     WHY ASKED: Performance question — shows you care about optimization.

A:  "VStack renders ALL its children at once — even off-screen.
    LazyVStack renders children ONLY when they appear on screen.

    VStack — use for small, fixed number of items (< 20)
    LazyVStack — use for long scrollable lists (100+ items)

    In my Quran reader (Azaan Pro), I used LazyVStack to
    load 6236 verses — only rendering visible verses.
    This reduced memory usage by 60% and eliminated
    scroll lag completely.

    Rule: If you have a ScrollView with many items,
    always prefer LazyVStack or LazyHStack."

