Q15. What is Task and TaskGroup in SwiftUI/Swift Concurrency?
     WHY ASKED: Modern concurrency — highly asked in 2024-2025.

A:  "Task — runs async work from sync context:
    .onAppear {
        Task {
            await loadPrayerTimes()
        }
    }

    Task.detached — runs independently of current context.

    TaskGroup — run multiple async tasks IN PARALLEL:
    await withTaskGroup(of: Double.self) { group in
        group.addTask { await fetchFajrTime() }
        group.addTask { await fetchDhuhrTime() }
        group.addTask { await fetchMaghribTime() }
        // all 3 run simultaneously — faster than sequential
    }

    In my app, I used TaskGroup to fetch prayer times,
    Hijri calendar, and weather simultaneously — reduced
    loading time from 3 seconds to under 1 second."

