Q17. Explain MVVM architecture with a real example.
     WHY ASKED: Most companies use MVVM — must know deeply.

A:  "MVVM = Model + View + ViewModel

    Model — raw data:
    struct Calorie: Codable { var food: String; var amount: Int }

    ViewModel — business logic + data binding:
    @Observable class CalorieViewModel {
        var calories: [Calorie] = []
        var totalCalories: Int { calories.reduce(0) { $0 + $1.amount } }
        func addCalorie(_ item: Calorie) { calories.append(item) }
    }

    View — only displays, zero logic:
    struct CalorieView: View {
        @State var vm = CalorieViewModel()
        var body: some View {
            Text('Total: \(vm.totalCalories) kcal')
        }
    }

    Benefits I've seen in my apps:
    - ViewModel is testable without UI
    - View stays clean and simple
    - Easy to swap data source (Firebase vs local)
    without changing the View at all."

