Q21. What is REPOSITORY PATTERN?
     WHY ASKED: Data layer architecture — asked in product companies.

A:  "Repository pattern abstracts the data source behind
    a protocol — so ViewModel doesn't care whether data
    comes from Firebase, CoreData, or a REST API.

    protocol CalorieRepository {
        func fetchCalories() async throws -> [Calorie]
        func save(_ calorie: Calorie) async throws
    }

    class FirebaseCalorieRepository: CalorieRepository {
        func fetchCalories() async throws -> [Calorie] {
            // fetch from Firestore
        }
    }

    class LocalCalorieRepository: CalorieRepository {
        func fetchCalories() async throws -> [Calorie] {
            // fetch from CoreData
        }
    }

    ViewModel uses only the protocol — can swap data source
    without changing a single line of ViewModel code.
    I use this in Count My Calories for offline support
    with CoreData fallback when there's no internet."

