Q22. What is SOLID Principles in iOS development?
     WHY ASKED: Code quality question — asked in senior roles.

A:  "SOLID is 5 principles for clean, maintainable code:

    S — Single Responsibility: One class, one job.
        PrayerCalculator only calculates, not saves.

    O — Open/Closed: Open for extension, closed for modification.
        Add new prayer calculation method without changing
        existing code.

    L — Liskov Substitution: Subclasses replaceable by parent.
        MockFirebase can replace real Firebase anywhere.

    I — Interface Segregation: Small focused protocols.
        Calculable, Saveable, Fetchable separately
        (not one giant DataManagerProtocol).

    D — Dependency Inversion: Depend on abstractions not
        concrete classes. (See Q19 — Dependency Injection)

    I follow SOLID actively — my code reviews focus on
    checking Single Responsibility and Dependency Inversion
    especially."

