Q28. How do you handle OFFLINE SUPPORT in iOS apps?
     WHY ASKED: Real-world app quality question — senior roles ask this.

A:  "Offline support strategy I follow:

    1. Local cache first:
       Check CoreData/UserDefaults before making network call.
       Show cached data immediately, refresh in background.

    2. Network monitoring with NWPathMonitor:
       let monitor = NWPathMonitor()
       monitor.pathUpdateHandler = { path in
           isOnline = path.status == .satisfied
       }

    3. Queue offline actions:
       Store pending operations locally, execute when
       connection restores.

    4. Firebase offline persistence:
       Firestore.firestore().settings.isPersistenceEnabled = true
       // Auto-caches data and syncs when back online

    In Azaan Pro, prayer times and Quran data are cached
    locally so the app works perfectly without internet.
    Only real-time features (like new Duas) require connection."

