Q31. What is Test Driven Development (TDD)?
     WHY ASKED: Development methodology — asked in agile teams.

A:  "TDD means writing tests BEFORE writing actual code.

    Red-Green-Refactor cycle:
    1. RED   — write a failing test for new feature
    2. GREEN — write minimum code to make test pass
    3. REFACTOR — clean up code while keeping test green

    Benefits:
    - Forces clear thinking about requirements upfront
    - Naturally produces testable, decoupled code
    - Confidence to refactor without breaking features

    For my Zakat calculator, I wrote tests first:
    XCTAssertEqual(zakatCalc.calculate(assets: 100000), 2500)
    Then implemented the logic to pass it.
    The tests caught a Nisab threshold bug immediately."

