Q32. What is Mocking in iOS testing?
     WHY ASKED: Advanced testing — senior level question.

A:  "Mocking means replacing real dependencies (network, database)
    with fake objects during testing.

    protocol PrayerServiceProtocol {
        func fetchTimes() async throws -> [PrayerTime]
    }

    class MockPrayerService: PrayerServiceProtocol {
        func fetchTimes() async throws -> [PrayerTime] {
            return [PrayerTime(name: 'Fajr', time: '05:30')] // fake data
        }
    }

    // Test uses mock — no real network call needed:
    let vm = PrayerViewModel(service: MockPrayerService())

    Benefits:
    - Tests run fast (no actual network)
    - Tests are reliable (no flaky network dependency)
    - Can simulate error cases easily

    This is why Dependency Injection (Q19) is so important
    — without it, mocking is impossible."

