Q46. What is SWIFT CONCURRENCY vs OperationQueue vs GCD?
     WHY ASKED: Concurrency evolution — shows you know history.

A:  "Evolution of concurrency in iOS:

    GCD (Grand Central Dispatch) — 2009:
    DispatchQueue.global().async { /* background */ }
    DispatchQueue.main.async { /* UI update */ }
    Low-level, C-based API.

    OperationQueue — more control, cancellable:
    let op = BlockOperation { self.processData() }
    op.cancel() // can cancel
    queue.addOperation(op)

    Swift Concurrency async/await — 2021 (BEST):
    let data = try await fetchData() // clean, readable
    async let a = fetchA()
    async let b = fetchB()
    let (resultA, resultB) = await (a, b) // parallel!

    Swift Concurrency wins because:
    - Readable linear code (no pyramid of doom)
    - Built-in cancellation with Task.cancel()
    - Compile-time safety with actors
    - Structured — child tasks auto-cancel with parent

    I have migrated my apps from GCD to async/await
    — code reduced by 40%, zero threading bugs."

